1 (2) THE COMPTROLLER MAY MAKE AN ASSESSMENT AGAINST THE
2 QUALIFIED BUSINESS ENTITY TO RECAPTURE ANY AMOUNT OF THE TAX CREDIT
3 THAT THE BUSINESS HAS CLAIMED.
4 (H) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1, 2028, THE SECRETARY SHALL REPORT TO
5 THE GOVERNOR AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
6 ARTICLE, THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY ON THE TAX CREDIT CERTIFICATES ISSUED
7 UNDER THIS SECTION AND THE STATUS OF ANY QUALIFIED BUSINESS ENTITY THAT
8 RECEIVED A CREDIT.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
10 (a) There is a Business Relocation Council.
11 (b) The Council consists of the following members:
12 (1) the Secretary of Commerce, or the Secretary’s designee;
13 (2) the Comptroller, or the Comptroller’s designee; and
14 (3) the Secretary of Labor, or the Secretary’s designee.
15 (c) The Secretary of Commerce, or the Secretary’s designee, shall be the chair of
16 the Council.
17 (d) The Department of Commerce shall provide staff for the Council.
18 (e) A member of the Council:
19 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Council; but
20 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
21 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
22 (f) The Council shall:
23 (1) advertise the income tax credit established under § 10–758 of the
24 Tax – General Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act, to other states nationwide; and
25 (2) establish, as necessary, subcommittees consisting of members of the
26 Council, experts in fields related to business relocation issues, and interested parties to
27 address or study specific issues pertaining to the Council’s duties.
28 (g) On or before December 31, 2028, the Council shall report on its efforts to the
29 Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the General
30 Assembly.

